“relevant agency” means a body or agency that is for the time being 
responsible in Malaysia for the enforcement of any federal law which 
is applicable in the Malaysian Maritime Zone;

“territorial  sea”  means  the  territorial  waters  of  Malaysia  as 
determined  in  accordance  with  the  Emergency  (Essential  Powers) 
Ordinance, No. 7 1969 [P.U.(A)307A/1969];

“internal  waters”  means  any  areas  of  the  sea  that  are  on  the 
landward  side  of  the  baselines  from  which  the  breadth  of  the 
territorial sea of Malaysia is measured;

“exclusive economic zone” means the exclusive economic zone of 
Malaysia as determined in accordance with the Exclusive Economic 
Zone Act 1984 [Act 311];

(a)  may be paid such allowances as may be determined by the 
Minister  after  consultation  with  the  Minister  of  Finance; 
and

(d)  to lend assistance in any criminal matters on a request by a 
foreign  State  as  provided  under  the  Mutual  Assistance  in 
Criminal Matters Act 2002 [Act 621];

(b)  to  stop,  enter,  board,  inspect  and  search  any  place, 
structure,  vessel  or  aircraft  and  to  detain  any  vessel  or 
aircraft;

(d)  to investigate any offence which it has reason to believe is 
being committed, or is about to be committed or has been 
committed;

(g)  to dispose of any fish, article, device, goods, vessel, aircraft 
or  any  other  item  relating  to  any  offence  which  has  been 
committed or it has reason to believe has been committed;

(g)  the  loading  or  unloading  of  any  commodity,  currency  or 
person  contrary  to  the  customs,  fiscal,  immigration  or 
health laws of Malaysia;
